JFrameMBTAHelper - Class in UI
The graphics for the application; Sets up the JFrame for the JPanels used in the rest of the application
JFrameMBTAHelper() - Constructor for class UI.JFrameMBTAHelper
Sets up the dimensions of the JFrame; Sets up all the tabs for the different functions of the application;
JPanelChangeData - Class in UI
JPanel in which the user chooses the source of the data.
JPanelChangeData() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelChangeData
Sets up RadioButtons to allow user to select either Live Data or Local Files; Sets up Buttons and action listeners to allow for users to select Local Files to use as data for the Blue, Orange, and Red lines.
JPanelLineColorSelector - Class in UI
JPanel in which user selects the Line Color; Used in JPanels where a line needs to be selected, with the exception of data source selection.
JPanelLineColorSelector(ActionListener, ActionListener, ActionListener) - Constructor for class UI.JPanelLineColorSelector
Sets up buttons for the Blue, Orange, and Red lines; Button behaves differently based upon the ActionListener parameters
JPanelMap - Class in UI
JPanel that displays a map of the MBTA T System.
JPanelMap() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelMap
Sets up the map image; Sets up the JPanel to be scrollable
JPanelNextArrival - Class in UI
JPanel used for the NextArrival functionality; User selects a Line Color, and the stops for which he/she wishes to view the next train arrivals
JPanelNextArrival() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelNextArrival
Sets up StopSelector JPanel; Sets up "Go" button and its ActionListener; Sets up the results panel in which NextArrivals are printed
JPanelPlanTrip - Class in UI
JPanel for the Plan Trip (Find Routes) functionality
JPanelPlanTrip() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelPlanTrip
Sets up StopSelector, TimePicker, and TripSelector JPanels; Sets up "Go" button and its ActionListener; Sets up result panel in which route information is printed;
JPanelStopSelector - Class in UI
JPanel for selecting stops; Used in NextArrivals and PlanTrip panels
JPanelStopSelector() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelStopSelector
Sets up ActionListeners for Blue, Orange, and Red Lines Sets up stops for Blue, Orange, and Red Lines Sets up "Add" and "Remove" Buttons and their Actions Sets up "Go" button and its Action
JPanelTimePicker - Class in UI
JPanel for selecting a time
JPanelTimePicker(String) - Constructor for class UI.JPanelTimePicker
Sets up spinner for time selection Sets up flag, stating if the panel is to be used
JPanelTrainLocations - Class in UI
JPanel used for the (Find) Train Locations functionality
JPanelTrainLocations() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelTrainLocations
Uses the LineColorSelector JPanel; Sets up the ActionListeners for the Blue, Orange, and Red line buttons; Sets up the result panel in which the train locations are printed
JPanelTrainStops - Class in UI
JPanel for finding the names of all stops on a line
JPanelTrainStops() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelTrainStops
Uses LineColorSelector; Sets up the ActionListeners for the Blue, Orange, and Red buttons Sets up the results panel in which all the names of the stops are printed
JPanelTripSelector - Class in UI
JPanel used to select all the options for finding a route
JPanelTripSelector() - Constructor for class UI.JPanelTripSelector
Inherits fields and methods from JPanelStopSelector
JSONReader - Class in Data
The JSONReader parses the MBTA data into the different Data classes.
JSONReader(Constants.DATA_SOURCE_SELECTOR, Constants.LINE_COLOR_SELECTOR) - Constructor for class Data.JSONReader
JSONReader constructor; The JSONReader gets built based on the source, and provided line color.
